          "text": "Discussion",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method is optional, but if implemented it will be called during the course of unified text checking via the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSSpellChecker"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspellchecker/1532957-checkspellingofstring"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " and "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsspellchecker/1526261-requestcheckingofstring"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " methods.  This allows spelling and grammar checking to be performed simultaneously, which can be significantly more efficient, and allows the delegate to return autocorrection results as well."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "If this method is not implemented, then unified text checking will call the separate spelling and grammar checking methods instead."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "This method may be called repeatedly with strings representing different subranges of the string that was originally requested to be checked; the offset argument represents the offset of the portion passed in to this method within that original string, and should be added to the origin of the range in any "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/foundation/nstextcheckingresult"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " returned."
            }
          ]
        }
